Program: Outlook
Title: 21/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00tbs76
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 22 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the man fleeing persecution in China who was held for four years in Guantanamo Bay and is now working as a pizza chef in Albania. Also, Matthew meets Martin Spinelli, the American man whose wife was killed and young son seriously injured in a motorway crash, but Martin says the tragedy has made him a better man - he has written about his experiences in a book entitled After The Crash. Show less